{"id":261,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":261,"title":"Centurion","subtitle":"","short_title":"Centurion","uri":"/scriptures/bd/centurion","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/centurion.t1","order":".000.703"},[".title","Centurion"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/centurion.p1","order":".000.704"},"An officer of the Roman army, in command of a century, or company of 100 men, forming one-sixtieth part of a Roman legion. In New Testament times the legions were not up to their full strength, and a century varied from 50 to 100 men. At least five centurions are mentioned in the New Testament, of which perhaps the best known is Cornelius (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/10.1-35"},"Acts 10:1–35"],"). See also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/8.8-10"},"Matt. 8:8–10"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/27.54"},"27:54"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/15.39"},"Mark 15:39"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/7.1-9"},"Luke 7:1–9"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/23.47"},"23:47"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/27.1"},"Acts 27:1"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/28.16"},"28:16"],"."]]],"refs":null}
